beer.beer_description:
Pale Ale brewed with Saaz and Victoria Hops.

Introducing Cypher 101 â€“ a sessionable, unfiltered pale ale thatâ€™s perfect for easy-drinking moments. We kick things off with just a touch of Saaz hops in the boil, giving the beer a nostalgic, earthy bitterness to balance out the juicy tropical flavours.

Next, we bring in Victoria Hops from Ryefield on the South Coast, used primarily in the dry hopping stage to deliver a vibrant hit of mango, passionfruit, and blueberry. These hops transform this brew into a smooth, crushable juice bomb thatâ€™s bursting with fresh, tropical goodness.

At only 3.5% ABV, Cypher 101 is full of flavour without the heavy punch, making it perfect for long afternoons.

Double Dry-hopped Aussie Pale Ale: Made exclusively using ingredients from Voyager Craft Malt and Hop Products Australia, we give you our Aussie Pale Ale. Loaded with hops layered on a soft malt base. This all-Aussie affair is one for a good olâ€™ session. Dry hopped at three different stages of fermentation, the beer brings big notes of lemon-lime slushie, orange and fresh cut pineapple. Perfect for a pint... or a shoe!

Unfiltered Double Dry Hopped India Pale Ale

Firesprite is the velvet sofa of our collection. If youâ€™re still on your journey into the craft world this beer is for you. Itâ€™s bright, warm and sumptuous but still light on bitterness. Loaded with Cascade, Centennial and Amarillo on the hot side only, to give a delicious citrus and pine kick, this beer holds balance and drinkability front and centre.

A bold dark ale with big hints of coffee and chocolate, balanced by a firm bitterness and rich sweetness, which gives this beer a great drinkability. 

Flavoured late on the hot side with Taiheke (NZ Cascade). This beer has a great American stout quality. Have a sip straight from the tap, then let it warm up to really experience the complexity this beer has to offer.
Brewed with Simcoe, Simcoe Cryo, Krush, Krush Hyperboost. Fermented with W34/70

A fruited sour ale brewed with lactose and infused with vanilla. Then gently conditioned on mountains of peach and mango to create a smooth, tart and creamy juice box.

A traditional take on a classic style, amplified with a new school aroma hop.
Brewed with a 100% pale pilsner malt base, to showcase the very best flavors and aromas that malt has to offer. Backed by a structured bittering from Spalter Select hops and topped off with a flavour addition from Callista. Notes of bready goodness topped with a noble spice and subtle hints of citrus and red berry. A pint of the good stuff is all you need!

For our first anniversary, we planned to brew a big juicy NEIPA with a heavy, hazy base, some exciting hops and flowable hop products. We also thought it would be fun to pair this exact hop bill against a modern WCIPA version, to see exactly how much the often-overlooked yeast and malt play a role in terms of overall hop expression.
Introducing â€˜Oneâ€™ and â€˜One For Good Luckâ€™ Cypher Brewing Coâ€™s first anniversary ales.
Drink side by side to get the full effect of how these beers express their unique yet similar qualities.
Hops: Citra, Citra 702, Citra Spectrum, Riwaka, Riwaka SubZero Hop kief, Mosaic, Azacca

West Coast India Pale Ale brewed with Citra, Citra Lupomax and Eclipse. With the addition of the new Euphorics Pineapple Paradise and Pomelo Daydream blends from HPA. Brewed with less bitterness than your usual WC IPA. To really let the Euphorics shine.

Triple Dry Hopped India Pale Ale brewed with Citra, Peacharine, Motueka Cryo and Galaxy Quantum Brite.

Get outta here! Look for yourself. Coz we definitely don't know nuthinâ€™ about no West Coast IPAs for sale around here.

Looks can be deceiving. This rich, dark Stout sits at five percent but packs a mouthful reminiscent of the Imperial kind. Thick and silky from additions of oats and lactose with tones of chewy choc-caramel biscuit, layered between wafts of sticky date pudding and splashes of roast coffee to balance it all out.

Welcome to the Chaos Realm. A series where we take on the infinite possibilities of flavour. Volume One has been fermented with cherries and conditioned on coconut. 

Come and wrap your laughing gear around this liquid cherry ripe... Or is it bounty??

This refreshing sour balances tart fruitiness and jammy sweetness with maximum drinkability. Big aromas of ice cream parlour and bright jammy raspberry sauce being slathered over a bowl of creamy vanilla ice cream, finished off with a sprinkle of nuts.   
Hits the sweet spot!

Behold! The champ is here! Pat Baggoley has taken out the annual Cypher/Canberra Brewers  24â€™ competition with his Red IPA. A classic mix of Citra and Simcoe over a base of chewy malts. Pat won the right to brew his recipe on our system, working directly with Matty to scale it up and get his hands dirty on brew day.  A local beer advocate, educating fellow Canberra Brewers and running BJCP judging courses, we couldnâ€™t think of a better candidate.  Cheers to you Pat! Hope we did it justice mate!
